    <summary><span data-ttu-id="24324-101">允许应用程序在网络接口 Internet 协议 (IP) 地址（也称为网卡或适配器）更改时接收通知。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="24324-101">Allows applications to receive notification when the Internet Protocol (IP) address of a network interface, also called a network card or adapter, changes.</span></span></summary>
    <remarks>
      <format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="24324-102"><xref:System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkChange> 类通过引发 <xref:System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkChange.NetworkAddressChanged> 事件来提供地址更改通知。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="24324-102">The <xref:System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkChange> class provides address change notification by raising <xref:System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkChange.NetworkAddressChanged> events.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="24324-103">接口地址可能因多种原因而变化，如断开连接的网络电缆、远离无线局域网的范围或硬件故障。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="24324-103">An interface address can change for many reasons, such as a disconnected network cable, moving out of range of a wireless Local Area Network, or hardware failure.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="24324-104">若要接收通知，必须标识应用程序的事件处理程序，这些处理程序是每次引发事件时执行特定于应用程序的任务的一个或多个方法。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="24324-104">To receive notification, you must identify your application's event handlers, which are one or more methods that perform your application-specific tasks each time the event is raised.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="24324-105">若要让 <xref:System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkChange> 对象在发生 <xref:System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkChange.NetworkAddressChanged> 事件时调用事件处理方法，必须将方法与 <xref:System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkAddressChangedEventHandler> 委托相关联，并将此委托添加到事件。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="24324-105">To have a <xref:System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkChange> object call your event-handling methods when a <xref:System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkChange.NetworkAddressChanged> event occurs, you must associate the methods with a <xref:System.Net.NetworkInformation.NetworkAddressChangedEventHandler> delegate, and add this delegate to the event.</span></span>  
  
   
  
